'''Ryan Isaac Mendes da Graça''' ({{IPA|pt|ʀi.ˈɐ̃<!----Although “Ryan” is an anglicised Irish name, the name of this player is usually pronounced [ʀi.ˈɐ̃]----> i.ˈzak ˈmẽ.dɨʒ dɐ ˈɡɾa.sɐ|lang}}<!----Although “Ryan” is an anglicised Irish name, the name of this player is usually pronounced [ʀi.ˈɐ̃]---->; born 8 January 1990) is a [[Cape Verde]]an professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[winger (association football)|winger]] for [[TFF 1. Lig]] club [[Iğdır F.K.|Iğdır]] and the [[Cape Verde national football team|Cape Verde national team]].

He spent most of his club career in France with [[Le Havre AC|Le Havre]] and [[Lille OSC|Lille]], and in the [[UAE Pro League]] with [[Sharjah FC|Sharjah]] and [[Al-Nasr SC (Dubai)|Al-Nasr]]. He also had brief spells in England's [[EFL Championship|Championship]] with [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]], and the Turkish [[Süper Lig]] with [[Kayserispor]] and Fatih Karagümrük.

Mendes made his senior international debut for [[Cape Verde national football team|Cape Verde]] in 2010, earning over 90 [[Cap (sport)|caps]]. He represented the nation at the [[Africa Cup of Nations]] in [[2013 Africa Cup of Nations|2013]], [[2015 Africa Cup of Nations|2015]], [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations|2021]] and [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations|2023]].

He is Cape Verde’s [[Cape Verde national football team#Most appearances|most capped player]] and [[Cape Verde national football team#Top goalscorers|top goalscorer]].

==Club career==
===Le Havre===
Born in [[Mindelo]], [[São Vicente, Cape Verde|São Vicente]], Mendes began his career with hometown club [[Batuque FC]]. In 2008 he was sold to [[Le Havre AC]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.paris-normandie.fr/index.php/cms/13/article/192098/Mendes_le_but_de_sa_vie|title=Actualité à la une en Normandie, toutes les informations locales|website=www.paris-normandie.fr|language=fr-FR|access-date=28 March 2018|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://archive.today/20120906144935/http://www.paris-normandie.fr/index.php/cms/13/article/192098/Mendes_le_but_de_sa_vie|archive-date=6 September 2012}}</ref> with whom he played his first game in [[Ligue 1]] on 13 May 2009 against [[AS Saint-Étienne]], as a late substitute for [[Maxime Baca]] in a 4–2 home loss.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.fussballdaten.de/frankreich/2009/35/lehavre-stetienne/ | title = Ryan Mendes Da Graca | language = de | publisher = fussballdaten.de | access-date =26 May 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Résultat et résumé Le Havre - Saint-Étienne, Ligue 1, 35e journée, Mercredi 13 Mai 2009 |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/match-direct/ligue-1/2008-2009/le-havre-asse-live/128037 |access-date=1 December 2021 |work=L'Équipe |date=13 May 2009 |language=French}}</ref> He was monitored by [[Leicester City]] scout [[Steve Walsh (scout)|Steve Walsh]], who instead signed teammate [[Riyad Mahrez]] to the club.<ref>{{cite news|title=Leicester City star Riyad Mahrez not target of original scouting mission says head of recruitment|url=http://www.leicestermercury.co.uk/Riyad-target-scouting-mission/story-28029571-detail/story.html|access-date=26 April 2016|work=Leicester Mercury|date=22 October 2015|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151129020313/http://www.leicestermercury.co.uk/Riyad-target-scouting-mission/story-28029571-detail/story.html|archive-date=29 November 2015}}</ref>

In the [[2011–12 Ligue 2|2011–12]] [[Ligue 2]], Mendes was joint third top scorer with 13 goals.<ref>{{cite news |title=Ligue 2. Fauré double Ghilas sur le fil pour le titre de meilleur buteur |url=https://www.ouest-france.fr/sport/football/ligue-2-faure-double-ghilas-sur-le-fil-pour-le-titre-de-meilleur-buteur-35007 |access-date=1 December 2021 |work=Ouest-France |date=18 May 2012 |language=French}}</ref>

===Lille===
On 1 September 2012, Mendes returned to Ligue 1 on a four-year deal at [[Lille OSC|Lille]]. He joined for a €3 million fee – the club was in a good financial place after the sale of [[Eden Hazard]] to Chelsea – and his monthly salary rose from €7,000 to €120,000.<ref>{{cite news |title=Losc: Salaire, indemnité, les chiffres du transfert de Ryan Mendes ! |url=https://www.sportune.fr/sport-business/losc-salaire-indemnite-les-chiffres-du-transfert-de-ryan-mendes-73121 |access-date=1 December 2021 |publisher=Sportune |date=1 September 2012 |language=French}}</ref> He missed the second half of his first season after having surgery on a right ankle tendon and remained on the sidelines until December 2013. He told the league's website that he was not going to retire despite the injuries.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Mondal|first1=Subhankar|title=Lille's Ryan Mendes dismisses retirement talks|url=http://www.sportsmole.co.uk/football/lille/news/mendes-dismisses-retirement-talks_119200.html|access-date=10 September 2017|publisher=Sports Mole|date=20 November 2013}}</ref>

Mendes's opportunities at Lille were reduced after the dismissal of manager [[Rudi Garcia]] in 2013.<ref name=aiming/> On 4 September 2015, Mendes joined English side [[Nottingham Forest]] on a season-long loan.<ref>{{cite news|title=Nelson Oliveira and Ryan Mendes join Nottingham Forest on loan|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/34157304|access-date=28 September 2015|publisher=BBC Sport|date=4 September 2015}}</ref> He scored his first goal for the club twenty days later, opening a 1–1 draw with [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Huddersfield 1–1 Nottm Forest|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/34275768|access-date=28 September 2015|publisher=BBC Sport|date=24 September 2015|first=Gary|last=Smee}}</ref>

===Later career===
On 31 January 2017, Mendes signed for [[Kayserispor]] – ranked 17th in Turkey's [[Süper Lig]] – until the summer of 2020.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Martins |first1=Sébastien |title=OFFICIEL : Ryan Mendes quitte Lille |url=https://www.goal.com/fr/news/29/ligue-1/2017/01/31/32161032/officiel-ryan-mendes-quitte-lille |access-date=1 December 2021 |publisher=Goal |date=31 January 2017 |language=French}}</ref> In July 2018, he terminated his deal and moved to [[Sharjah FC]] of the [[UAE Pro League]] on a three-year deal.<ref>{{cite news |title=Ryan Mendes leaves Kayserispor for UAE club |url=https://www.turkishfootballnews.com/2018/07/03/ryan-mendes-leaves-kayserispor-uae-club/ |access-date=1 December 2021 |publisher=Turkish Football News |date=3 July 2018}}</ref> He won the league in his first season.<ref name=aiming>{{cite web|last1=Lomas|first1=Mark|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/47975321|title=Cape Verde's Ryan Mendes aiming for unlikely UAE title|date=24 April 2019|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref><ref name=uae>{{cite news |title=Sharjah crowned champions; Dibba and Emirates relegated |url=https://www.gulftoday.ae/sport/2019/05/26/sharjah-crowned-champions-dibba-and-emirates-relegated |access-date=1 December 2021 |publisher=Gulf Today |date=26 May 2019}}</ref>

Remaining in the United Arab Emirates, Mendes moved to [[Al-Nasr SC (Dubai)|Al-Nasr SC]] in [[Dubai]] on a two-year contract in July 2020.<ref>{{cite news |title=Futebol: Ryan Mendes troca o Al Sharjah pelo AL Nasr [''sic''] |url=https://www.anacao.cv/noticia/2020/07/08/futebol-ryan-mendes-troca-o-al-sharjah-pelo-al-nasr/ |access-date=1 December 2021 |work=A Nação |date=8 July 2020 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> On 10 August 2023, he went back to Turkey's top division and signed a two-year contract with [[Fatih Karagümrük S.K.|Fatih Karagümrük]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ntvspor.net/futbol/fatih-karagumruk-ten-sol-kanat-transferi-64d4a9034094b30049c8d51c|title=Fatih Karagümrük'ten sol kanat transferi|last=|first=|date=10 August 2023|website=ntvspor.net|publisher=|language=tr|access-date=27 August 2023}}</ref>

==International career==
Mendes was a member of the [[Cape Verde national football team|Cape Verde under-21 national team]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://criolosports.blogspot.com/2009/05/ryan-mendes-estreia-se-no-le-havre.html|title=Criolosports.com: Ryan Mendes estreia-se no Le Havre|last=Criolosports|date=15 May 2009|website=Criolosports.com|access-date=28 March 2018}}</ref> and played formerly with the under-16s an international tournament in Gonfreville-L'Orcher.

He made his debut for the senior team on 11 August 2010, as a 58th-minute substitute for [[Babanco]] in a 1–0 friendly loss away to [[Senegal national football team|Senegal]]. His first international goal was scored on 8 October 2011, in a 2–1 loss at [[Zimbabwe]] in [[2012 Africa Cup of Nations]] [[2012 Africa Cup of Nations qualification|qualification]].<ref>{{NFT|39690}}</ref>

In [[2013 Africa Cup of Nations]] [[2013 Africa Cup of Nations qualification|qualification]], Mendes scored three goals in two wins over [[Madagascar national football team|Madagascar]].<ref>{{cite news |title=CAN 2013: Le Cap Vert domine Madagascar |url=https://www.afrik-foot.com/can-2013-le-cap-vert-domine-madagascar |access-date=1 December 2021 |date=29 February 2012 |language=French}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=CAN 2013 : Le Cap Vert écarte Madagascar |url=https://www.afrik-foot.com/can-2013-le-cap-vert-ecarte-madagascar |access-date=1 December 2021 |publisher=Afrik Foot |date=16 June 2012 |language=French}}</ref> At the finals in South Africa, Cape Verde's first major tournament, he played all four games of a run to the quarter-finals.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Fottrell |first1=Stephen |title=South Africa 0–0 Cape Verde |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/21042985 |access-date=1 December 2021 |date=19 January 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Fottrell |first1=Stephen |title=Morocco 1–1 Cape Verde Islands |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/21037955 |access-date=1 December 2021 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=23 January 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Fottrell |first1=Stephen |title=Cape Verde 2–1 Angola |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/21037955 |access-date=1 December 2021 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=27 January 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Hughes |first1=Ian |title=Ghana 2–0 Cape Verde |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/21294305 |access-date=1 December 2021 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=2 February 2013}}</ref>

Mendes scored the decider on 10 September 2014 as Cape Verde won 2–1 against [[Zambia national football team|Zambia]] in [[Praia]], in [[2015 Africa Cup of Nations]] [[2015 Africa Cup of Nations qualification|qualification]].<ref>{{cite news |title=CAN: Zé Luís e Ryan Mendes dão triunfo a Cabo Verde |url=https://www.record.pt/internacional/detalhe/can-ze-luis-e-ryan-mendes-dao-triunfo-a-cabo-verde-903772 |access-date=1 December 2021 |work=Record |date=10 September 2014 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> He was called up for the finals in Equatorial Guinea,<ref>{{cite news |title=Cardoso da Silva: "Convocatória é correcta para Cabo Verde alcançar um bom resultado" |url=https://www.rfi.fr/pt/africa/20141224-cardoso-da-silva-convocatoria-e-correcta-para-cabo-verde-alcancar-um-bom-resultado |access-date=1 December 2021 |publisher=Radio France International |date=24 December 2014 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> playing in all three draws of a group-stage elimination.

In November 2020, he reached 50 international [[Cap (sport)|caps]], for which he was rewarded with a shirt and plaque the following March.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Furtado |first1=António |title=Ryan Mendes: 50 jogos pela seleção nacional de futebol |url=https://gaftsports.com/ryan-mendes-50-jogos-pela-selecao-nacional-de-futebol/ |access-date=1 December 2021 |publisher=Gaft Sports |date=25 March 2021 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> A year later, he was called up for the [[2021 Africa Cup of Nations]] in Cameroon<ref>{{cite news |title=Afcon 2021: Ethiopia and Cape Verde squads for finals in Cameroon |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/africa/59763245 |access-date=24 December 2021 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=23 December 2021}}</ref> and appeared in two of Cape Verde's matches at the tournament.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/player/matches/_/id/135216/team/2597/type/caf.nations/year/2021|title=RYAN MENDES|access-date=21 January 2024|website=ESPN}}</ref>

On 17 November 2023, he played his 62th international game in a 0–0 draw with [[Angola national football team|Angola]] in [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – CAF Group D|2026 World Cup qualification]] game, tying [[Babanco]]’s record to become Cape Verde joint most capped player.<ref>{{cite web |title=Seleção Nacional de Futebol: Ryan Mendes iguala feito de Babanco |url=https://rtc.cv/noticia/noticia-details/selecao-nacional-de-futebol-ryan-mendes-iguala-feito-de-babanco-12165#google_vignette |website=RTC.cv |access-date=3 December 2025}}</ref>

On 21 November 2023, in a 2–0 victory over [[Eswatini national football team|Eswatini]] in a [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – CAF Group D|2026 World Cup qualification]] game, he played his 63th international game, becoming Cape Verde [[Cape Verde national football team#Most appearances|sole most capped player]] and scored his 15th international goal and tied [[Héldon Ramos]] record to become Cape Verde joint top goalscorer.<ref>{{cite web |title=Futebol: Ryan Mendes iguala Heldon no topo dos melhores marcadores de sempre da seleção nacional |url=https://www.anacao.cv/noticia/2023/11/22/futebol-ryan-mendes-iguala-heldon-no-topo-dos-melhores-marcadores-de-sempre-da-selecao-nacional/ |website=A Nacão |access-date=3 December 2025}}</ref>

In December 2023, Mendes was named in Cape Verde's squad for his fourth [[Africa Cup of Nations]] – the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations|2023 tournament]] in the [[Ivory Coast]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/cape-verde-name-veterans-mendes-vozinha-african-cup-nations-squad-2023-12-29/|title=Cape Verde name veterans Mendes, Vozinha in African Cup of Nations squad|date=30 December 2023|access-date=21 January 2023|website=Reuters}}</ref>

He [[Captain (association football)|captained]] the team in their opening two matches of the tournament on 14 and 19 January 2024 – wins against [[Ghana national football team|Ghana]] (2–1), and [[Mozambique national football team|Mozambique]] (3–0) – scoring and being named [[Player of the match|man of the match]] in the latter.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cafonline.com/caf-africa-cup-of-nations/news/we-have-achieved-our-first-target-ryan-mendes-after-qualification/|title="We have achieved our first target" - Ryan Mendes after qualification|date=19 January 2024|access-date=21 January 2024|website=CAF Online}}</ref> 
The goal against Mozambique was his 16th international goal and he thus became Cape Verde’s [[Cape Verde national football team#Top goalscorers|sole top goalscorer]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Com 16 golos, Ryan Mendes torna-se no melhor marcador de sempre da história da seleção cabo-verdiana |url=https://www.boohmagazine.com/2024/01/com-16-golos-ryan-mendes-torna-se-no.html?m=1 |website=Booh Magazine |access-date=3 December 2025}}</ref>

He later scored the only goal from a penalty in a 1–0 victory over [[Mauritania national football team|Mauritania]], which qualified his country to the quarter-finals.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68052400 |title=Cape Verde 1–0 Mauritania |publisher=BBC Sport |date=29 January 2024 }}</ref>

